data.description: How about a touch of 'country' right in the middle of Frenchman's Bend?! This Acadian style home with 2629 HSF backs up to conservation land that will always give you a feeling of being out of the city! You can enjoy the views from your covered back patio while you're grilling on your gas grill from the outdoor cook area. When you step inside, the beautiful wood flooring paired with white and gray color palette is sure to catch your eye! Be sure to notice the butler's pantry leading from the kitchen to the dining room.  In addition, the walk in pantry provides oodles of space! The kitchen island with contrasting color adds a bit of style and the stainless appliances, microwave warming drawer, pot filler above the gas stove and vent hood provides functionality. You'll love the triple split floor plan - everyone has their own 'wing' of the house! The laundry room is conveniently located on the bedroom wing of the house. Do you need 4 bedrooms or 5? The upstairs bonus room with a closet could be a fifth bedroom, an office, play room or hobby/craft room - you decide! Stylish colors, beautiful wood floors, deep crown molding, high ceilings and open floor plan make this the home you want to call your own!
